RT @TooFarigh: A few afterthoughts on this interesting Space on the #NoorMukadam. 

Listen to women.
Don't be thinking about what you think she's saying. 
Listen to her.
Let her finish.
Listen to her concerns.
Don't evaluate the risk to her by how you'd react. You nor I, are in her shoes.
1/5 https://t.co/aAgKj8q5vk

Be realistic about what culture/society looks like around you. And acknowledge our (me & you) complicity in this issue. Finger-pointing to society leads to our own selves. So drastically change your stance and be intolerant of even a little sexism that you see.
#NoorMukadam 4/5

IMHO, the gruesomeness of the crime has a lot to do with the outrage. üëµroutinely endure pinching, grabbing, obscene gestures, & other non-lethal but quite demeaning treatment.

Be outraged at these indignities üßïface,  don't wait for something to kill us. #NoorMukadam  2/5
